# AWS Services Verification — Command Reference

Companion to the EKS command reference. Covers the managed services behind the portal.

> ⚠️ **Confirm your AWS account and region before every session** (`aws sts get-caller-identity`). Everything here is **read-only** — no `create`, `modify`, `delete`, `reboot`, or `failover` calls. Replace `<placeholders>` with real values.

For CloudWatch time ranges below, set:
```bash
export START=$(date -u -d '1 hour ago' +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)   # macOS: date -u -v-1H ...
export END=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)
```

---

## 1. RDS MySQL

```bash
# Core config: status, engine, HA, encryption, exposure
aws rds describe-db-instances --db-instance-identifier <id> \
  --query 'DBInstances[0].{Status:DBInstanceStatus,Engine:Engine,Version:EngineVersion,\
Class:DBInstanceClass,MultiAZ:MultiAZ,Encrypted:StorageEncrypted,\
Public:PubliclyAccessible,DeletionProtection:DeletionProtection}'

# Backups & recovery point
aws rds describe-db-instances --db-instance-identifier <id> \
  --query 'DBInstances[0].{Retention:BackupRetentionPeriod,Window:PreferredBackupWindow,\
LatestRestorable:LatestRestorableTime}'

# Recent automated snapshots exist
aws rds describe-db-snapshots --db-instance-identifier <id> --snapshot-type automated \
  --query 'reverse(sort_by(DBSnapshots,&SnapshotCreateTime))[:5].{Id:DBSnapshotIdentifier,Time:SnapshotCreateTime,Status:Status}'

# Live load: connections & CPU
aws cloudwatch get-metric-statistics --namespace AWS/RDS --metric-name DatabaseConnections \
  --dimensions Name=DBInstanceIdentifier,Value=<id> \
  --start-time $START --end-time $END --period 300 --statistics Average Maximum
aws cloudwatch get-metric-statistics --namespace AWS/RDS --metric-name CPUUtilization \
  --dimensions Name=DBInstanceIdentifier,Value=<id> \
  --start-time $START --end-time $END --period 300 --statistics Average Maximum
```

**Look for:** `available`; **Multi-AZ true** in prod; encrypted at rest; `PubliclyAccessible false`; deletion protection on; backup retention adequate (e.g. 7–35 days) with a recent `LatestRestorableTime`; connection count well below `max_connections`; the DB security group allows **only the app security group** on 3306 (see §9).

